                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d649">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/17914</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Letcher</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">El Paso</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-04-17T17:00:00-07:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 17, 1916, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>All troops apparently are being withdrawn from territory covered by American
                    soldiers and preparations are being made for these to go south, probably to
                    Parral.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Letcher</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
